investigation.title: Transcriptomic analysis of spleens from mice subjected to chronic low-dose radiation, hindlimb unloading or a combination of both
investigation.description: The purpose of this study was to evaluate transcriptional changes in mouse spleens using a ground-based model for spaceflight. This model includes prolonged unloading and low-dose irradiation.

project.funding: This study was supported by NASA grant NNX13AL97G and 80NSSC17K0693 to Xiao W Mao, and the sequencing analysis was funded by NASA Space Biology Program Office, Space Life and Physical Sciences Research and Applications Division through a collaborative effort with GeneLab.
